[[File:EscapefromAlcatrazbook.jpg|thumb|200px|Cover of the book]]
'''''Escape from Alcatraz''''' is a 1963 non-fiction book, written by [[J. Campbell Bruce]], about the history of [[Alcatraz Island|Alcatraz Penitentiary]] and the [[List of Alcatraz escape attempts|escape attempts]] made by the inmates. It was revised in 1976 and again in 2005.

Portions of this book concern [[June 1962 Alcatraz escape|the escape]] of [[Frank Morris (prisoner)|Frank Morris]] and brothers [[John Anglin (criminal)|John]] and [[Clarence Anglin]], which was the basis for the film ''[[Escape from Alcatraz (film)|Escape from Alcatraz]]'' in 1979.

