:''See [[Federal Street Theatre]] for an earlier theatre known also as the Boston Theatre'' The '''Boston Theatre''' was a theatre in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]. It was first built in 1854 and operated as a [[theatre]] until 1925. Productions included performances by [[Thurlow Bergen]],<ref name=clapp1899 /> [[Charles A. Bigelow]],<ref name=tompkins1908 /> [[Edwin Booth]],<ref>{{Citation |publisher = Stage Pub. Co. |publication-place = Boston |title = Playgoers' Year-Book |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL17937497M/The_playgoers'_year-book_for_1888. |author = Charles E. L. Wingate |publication-date = 1888 }}</ref> [[Anna Held]],<ref name=tompkins1908>{{Citation |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL7237383M/The_history_of_the_Boston_theatre_1854-1901 |author = Eugene Tompkins |publisher = Houghton Mifflin |publication-date = 1908 |publication-place = Boston |title = History of the Boston Theatre, 1854-1901 }}</ref> [[James O'Neill (actor)|James O'Neill]]<ref name=clapp1899>{{Citation |publisher = Dunlap Society |publication-place = New York |title = Players of the Present |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=i8U4AQAAMAAJ |volume=1 |author1 = John Bouvé Clapp |author2= Edwin Francis Edgett |publication-date = 1899 |oclc = 2623904 }}</ref> [[Jennie Kimball]], and others.
